{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Qzkf7ruufARuBQ6A7qKVzw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see important information from the logs:\n\n1. crdb-cluster-1 is having trouble connecting to crdb-cluster-0 (at `10.244.0.42`) and crdb-cluster-2 (at `10.244.0.41`) - I/O timeouts\n2. The HTTP server is starting at `127.0.0.1:8080` - this is the problem! The readiness probe is checking `http://:http/health?ready=1` which would check the pod's network interface, but the server is only bound to `127.0.0.1:8080`\n3. The server is listening only on localhost instead of all interfaces (`0.0.0.0`), so when the readiness probe tries to reach it from outside the container, the connection fails.\n\nLooking at the startup script more carefully, it conditionally sets `HTTP_ADDR` based on whether the pod is the first replica (`*-0`), binding to localhost for that one and `0.0.0.0` for the others. But the log shows even the first pod is binding to `127.0.0.1:8080`, which suggests the condition might not be evaluating as expected or there's something else overriding it. Looking at the actual log output, crdb-cluster-1 is starting its HTTP server at 127.0.0.1:8080 rather than 0.0.0.0:8080, which suggests the conditional logic in the StatefulSet command might not be evaluating as expected for that pod. The log also shows it's aware of the proper DNS name (crdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local), so there's a mismatch between what the command should be setting and what's actually happening. mean the DNS is resolving to an outdated IP that's no longer assigned to any pod. This points to a DNS caching issue or the headless service not being updated properly when pods are recreated.\n\nThe real problem though is the readiness probe—it's trying to reach the HTTP health endpoint, but the CockroachDB server is only listening on localhost, not on the pod's actual IP address. That's why the probe fails and the pod never becomes ready, even if the cluster itself could theoretically start up.\n\nLet me check the StatefulSet configuration to see what command is actually being executed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3846,"cache_read_input_tokens":29309,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3846},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f39a24d6-f279-4b08-a6aa-623bc4d0e523","uuid":"d6b57a71-447c-49f3-8f75-7ed61e2380d7","request_id":"req_011CccCVC2S2VKLVvY3thQQe"}
